<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:12pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:36pt; line-height:12pt; font-size:12pt; color:#000000">Item 8.01. &nbsp;<U>Other Events</U>.1</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:12pt; padding-left:36pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:36pt; line-height:12pt; font-size:12pt; color:#000000">Filed concurrently herewith are certain materials (the &#8220;Computational &nbsp;Materials&#148;) furnished to the Registrant by Greenwich Capital Markets, Inc. (the &#147;Underwriter&#148;) in respect of the HarborView Mortgage Loan Trust 2004-10, Mortgage Loan Pass-Through Certificates, Series 2004-10 (the &#147;Certificates&#148;). &nbsp;The Certificates are being offered pursuant to a prospectus supplement and the related prospectus, dated (together, the &#147;Prospectus&#148;), which are being filed with the Commission pursuant to Rule 424(b) under the Securities Act of 1933, as amended (the &#147;Act&#148;). &nbsp;The Certificates have been registered pursuant to the Act under a Registration Statement on Form S-3 (No. 333-120038-01) (the &#147;Registration Statement&#148;). &nbsp;The Computational Ma
terials are incorporated by reference in the Registration Statement.</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:12pt; padding-left:36pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:36pt; line-height:12pt; font-size:12pt; color:#000000">The Computational Materials were prepared solely by the Underwriter, and the Registrant did not prepare or participate (other than providing the background information concerning each underlying pool of assets upon which the Computational Materials are based to the Underwriter) in the preparation of the Computational Materials.</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:12pt; padding-left:36pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:36pt; line-height:12pt; font-size:12pt; color:#000000">Any statements or information contained in the Computational Materials shall be deemed to be modified or superseded for purposes of the Prospectus and the Registration Statement by statements or information contained in the Prospectus.</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:5pt; padding-left:36pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-36pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>________________________________________</P>

<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:4.5pt; margin-bottom:-9pt; padding-left:36pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0.7pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-36pt; line-height:9pt; font-size:9pt; color:#000000" align=justify><I>(1)</I></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:36pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0.7pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:9pt; font-size:9pt; color:#000000" align=justify><I>Distributions on the <A NAME="OLE_LINK8"></A>Class<A NAME="OLE_LINK7"></A> 1-A, Class 2-A, Class 3-A and Class 4-A Certificates will be primarily derived from the Group 1, Group 2, Group 3 and Group 4 Mortgage Loans, respectively. &nbsp;Class sizes are subject to final collateral pool size and rating agency approval and may increase or decrease by up to 10%.</I></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:4.5pt; margin-bottom:-9pt; padding-left:36pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-36pt; line-height:9pt; font-size:9pt; color:#000000" align=justify><I>(2)</I></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:36pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:9pt; font-size:9pt; color:#000000" align=justify><I>WAL and Payment Window for the Class 1-A and Class 2-A Certificates are shown to the Optional Call Date and to maturity (as described herein). &nbsp;WAL and Payment Window for the Class 3-A and Class 4-A Certificates are shown to the earlier of (i) the related Weighted Average Roll Date or (ii) the Optional Call Date and to maturity (as described herein). &nbsp;</I></P>
<A NAME="OLE_LINK14"></A><P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:4.5pt; margin-bottom:-9pt; padding-left:36pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0.7pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-36pt; line-height:9pt; font-size:9pt; color:#000000" align=justify><I>(3)</I></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:36pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0.7pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:9pt; font-size:9pt; color:#000000" align=justify><I>For every Distribution Date, the interest rate for each of the Class 1-A Certificates will be equal to the least of (i) One-Month LIBOR plus the related margin (which margin doubles after the &nbsp;first possible Optional Call Date), (ii) the related Net WAC Cap and (iii) 11.00%.</I></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:4.5pt; margin-bottom:-9pt; padding-left:36pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0.7pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-36pt; line-height:9pt; font-size:9pt; color:#000000" align=justify><I>(4)</I></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:36pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0.7pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:9pt; font-size:9pt; color:#000000" align=justify><I>For every Distribution Date, the interest rate for each of the Class 2-A Certificates will be equal to the least of (i) Six-Month LIBOR plus the related margin (which margin doubles after the first reset date following the first possible Optional Call Date), (ii) the related Net WAC Cap and (iii) 11.00%.</I></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:4.5pt; margin-bottom:-9pt; padding-left:36pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0.7pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-36pt; line-height:9pt; font-size:9pt; color:#000000" align=justify><I>(5)</I></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:36pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0.7pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:9pt; font-size:9pt; color:#000000" align=justify><I>For every Distribution Date, the interest rate for each of the Class 3-A and Class 4-A Certificates will be equal to (i) the Net WAC Rate of the Mortgage Loans in the related Mortgage Loan Group.</I></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>

<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>December 1, 2004.</P>

<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><BR></P>

<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>On or about December 22, 2004. </P>

<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>The 19th day of each month (or if such day is not a business day, the next succeeding business day), commencing in January 2005.</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><I>Certificates:</I></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>The &#147;<B><I>Senior Certificates</I></B>&#148; will consist of the Class 1-A, Class 2-A, Class 3-A and Class 4-A Certificates (collectively the <B><I>&#147;Class A Certificates&#148;</I></B>) and the Class X-1, Class X-2 and Class A-R Certificates. &nbsp;The Class B-1, Class B-2 and Class B-3 Certificates will be referred to herein as the &#147;<B><I>Senior Subordinate Certificates</I></B>&#148; and the Class B-4, Class B-5, and Class B-6 Certificates will be referred to herein as the &#147;<B><I>Junior Subordinate Certificates</I></B>,&#148; together with the Senior Subordinate Certificates, the &#147;<B><I>Subordinate Certificates</I></B>.&#148; &nbsp;The Senior Certificates and the Subordinate Certificates are collectively referred to herein as the &#147;<B><I>Certificates</I></B>.&#148; 
&nbsp;The Class A Certificates &nbsp;(the<B> </B>&#147;<B><I>Offered Certificates</I></B>&#148;) are being offered publicly.</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><I>Accrued Interest:</I></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>The price to be paid by investors for the <A NAME="OLE_LINK18"></A>Class 1-A and Class 2-A Certificates will not include accrued interest (settling flat). &nbsp;The price to be paid by investors for the Class 3-A and Class 4-A Certificates and the Senior Subordinates will include accrued interest from the Cut-off Date up to, but not including, the Closing Date (21 days). </P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><BR></P>

<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><I>Interest Accrual Period:</I></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>The interest accrual period with respect to the Class 1-A and Class 2-A Certificates for a given Distribution Date will be the period beginning with the 19th day of the month prior to such Distribution Date (or in the case of the first Distribution Date, the Closing Date) and ending on the 18th day of the month of such Distribution Date (on a 30/360 basis). &nbsp;The interest accrual period with respect to the Class 3-A and Class 4-A Certificates and the Senior Subordinate Certificates for a given Distribution Date will be the calendar month preceding the month in which such Distribution Date occurs (on a 30/360 basis). </P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><I>Registration:</I></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>The Offered Certificates will be made available in book-entry form through DTC. &nbsp;It is anticipated that the Offered Certificates will also be made available in book-entry form through Clearstream, Luxembourg and the Euroclear System.</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><I>Federal Tax Treatment:</I></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>It is anticipated that the Class A Certificates and Senior Subordinate Certificates will be treated as REMIC regular interests for federal tax income purposes. &nbsp;The Class A-R Certificate will be treated as a REMIC residual interest for tax purposes.</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><I>ERISA Eligibility:</I></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>The Class A Certificates and Senior Subordinate Certificates are expected to be ERISA eligible. &nbsp;Prospective investors should review with their legal advisors whether the purchase and holding of the Class A Certificates and Senior Subordinate Certificates could give rise to a transaction prohibited or not otherwise permissible under ERISA, the Internal Revenue Code or other similar laws. &nbsp;The Class A-R Certificate is not expected to be ERISA eligible.</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><I>SMMEA Treatment:</I></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>The Senior Certificates and Class B-1 Certificates are expected to constitute &#147;mortgage related securities&#148; for purposes of SMMEA. &nbsp;The Class B-2 and Class B-3 Certificates <B><I>will not</I> </B>constitute &#147;mortgage related securities&#148; for purposes of SMMEA.</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><I>Optional Termination:</I></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>The terms of the transaction allow for a termination of the Offered Certificates, which may be exercised once the aggregate principal balance of the Mortgage Loans is equal to or less than [10]% of the aggregate principal balance of the Mortgage Loans as of the Cut-off Date (the &#147;<B><I>Optional Call Date</I></B>&#148;).</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><I>Weighted Average</I></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><I>Roll Date:</I> </P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>For structuring the Weighted Average Roll Date with respect to the Group 3 and Group 4 Mortgage Loans is assumed to be the Distribution Date in September 2007 and September 2009, respectively.</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><I>Pricing Prepayment</I></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:-5.45pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><I>Speed:</I></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:-5.45pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>The Offered Certificates will be priced to the following prepayment pricing speeds:</P>
<I><P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:-5.45pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:36pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify></I>Group 1 and Group 2 Mortgage Loans: &nbsp;20% CPR</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:-5.45pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:36pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>Group 3 and Group 4 Mortgage Loans: &nbsp;25% CPR &nbsp;</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><BR></P>

<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><I>Mortgage Loans:</I></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>Collectively, the Group 1 Mortgage Loans, the Group 2 Mortgage Loans Group 3 Mortgage Loans and the Group 4 Mortgage Loans will be referred to as the &#147;<B><I>Mortgage Loans</I></B>&#148;. &nbsp;The aggregate principal balance of the Mortgage Loans as of the November 1, 2004 is approximately $743,006,847. &nbsp;</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><I><BR></I></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><B>It is anticipated that on the Closing Date, the characteristics of the Mortgage Loans as of the Cut-Off Date will be substantially similar to the characteristics of the Mortgage Loans &nbsp;as described and shown herein. &nbsp;The aggregate principal balance is expected to be subject to an increase or decrease of up to 10%.</B></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><I>Group 1</I></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><I>Mortgage Loans:</I></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>As of the Cut-off Date, the aggregate principal balance of the Group 1 Mortgage Loans described herein is approximately $162,810,841 (the &#147;Group 1 Mortgage Loans&#148;). The Group 1 Mortgage Loans are non-convertible, adjustable rate mortgage loans, all of which adjust based on 1 month or 6 month LIBOR. &nbsp;Each of the Group 1 Mortgage Loans has an original term to maturity of 15, 25 and 30 years. A portion of the Group 1 Mortgage Loans (see attached preliminary collateral summary) are scheduled to pay interest only for a term of approximately six months, five or ten years following origination. &nbsp;&nbsp;Thereafter, each such Mortgage Loan will pay scheduled principal, in addition to interest, in an amount sufficient to fully amortize such Mortgage Loans over its remaining term. &nbsp
;The Group 1 Mortgage Loans are secured by first liens on one- to four-family residential properties. &nbsp;See the attached preliminary collateral information. &nbsp;</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><I>Group 2 </I></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><I>Mortgage Loans:</I></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>As of the Cut-off Date, the aggregate principal balance of the Group 2 Mortgage Loans described herein is approximately $117,318,094 (the &#147;Group 2 Mortgage Loans&#148;). The Group 2 Mortgage Loans are non-convertible, adjustable rate mortgage loans, all of which adjust based on 6 month LIBOR. &nbsp;Each of the Group 2 Mortgage Loans has an original term to maturity of 30 years. A portion of the Group 2 Mortgage Loans (see attached preliminary collateral summary) are scheduled to pay interest only for a term of approximately five or ten years following origination. &nbsp;&nbsp;Thereafter, each such Mortgage Loan will pay scheduled principal, in addition to interest, in an amount sufficient to fully amortize such Mortgage Loans over its remaining term. &nbsp;The Group 2 Mortgage Loans are se
cured by first liens on one- to four-family residential properties. &nbsp;See the attached preliminary collateral information. &nbsp;</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><I>Group 3</I></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><I>Mortgage Loans:</I></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><I></I>As of the Cut-off Date, the aggregate principal balance of the Group 3 Mortgage Loans described herein is approximately $287,294,093 (the &#147;Group 3 Mortgage Loans&#148;). The Group 3 Mortgage Loans are non-convertible, adjustable rate mortgage loans, all of which adjust based on 6 month LIBOR, 12 month LIBOR or 1 Year CMT and all of which have initial rate adjustments primarily occurring approximately 3 years after the date of origination of each mortgage loan. &nbsp;Each of the Group 3 Mortgage Loans has an original term to maturity of 30 years. &nbsp;A portion of the Group 3 Mortgage Loans (see attached preliminary collateral summary) are scheduled to pay interest only for the first three or ten years. &nbsp;&nbsp;Thereafter, each such Mortgage Loan will pay scheduled principal, in
 addition to interest, in an amount sufficient to fully amortize such Mortgage Loans over its remaining term. &nbsp;The Group 3 Mortgage Loans are secured by first liens on one- to four-family residential properties. &nbsp;See the attached preliminary collateral information. &nbsp;</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><I><BR></I></P>

The Group 4 Mortgage Loans are non-convertible, adjustable rate mortgage loans, all of which adjust based on 6 month LIBOR, 12 month LIBOR or 1 Year CMT and all of which have initial rate adjustments primarily occurring approximately 5 years after the date of origination of each mortgage loan. &nbsp;Each of the Group 4 Mortgage Loans has an original term to maturity of 30 years. &nbsp;A portion of the Group 4 Mortgage Loans (see attached preliminary collateral summary) are scheduled to pay interest only for the first five or ten years. &nbsp;&nbsp;Thereafter, each such Mortgage Loan will pay scheduled principal, in 
addition to interest, in an amount sufficient to fully amortize such Mortgage Loans over its remaining term. &nbsp;The Group 4 Mortgage Loans are secured by first liens on one- to four-family residential properties. &nbsp;See the attached preliminary collateral information. &nbsp;</P>

<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>Senior/subordinate, shifting interest structure. &nbsp;The credit enhancement information shown below is subject to final rating agency approval.</P>

<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>Credit enhancement for the <U>Senior Certificates</U> will consist of the subordination of the Class B-1, Class B-2, Class B-3, Class B-4, Class B-5 and Class B-6 Certificates, initially [6.00]% total subordination.</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><I>Shifting Interest</I>:</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>Until the first Distribution Date occurring after December 2014, the Subordinate Certificates will be locked out from receipt of principal prepayments (unless the Senior Certificates are paid down to zero or the credit enhancement provided by the Subordinate Certificates has doubled prior to such date as described below). &nbsp;After such time and subject to standard collateral performance triggers (as described in the prospectus supplement), the Subordinate Certificates will receive their increasing portions of principal prepayments.</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><BR></P>

<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>January 2015 &#150; December 2015</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:207pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>30% Pro Rata Share</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>January 2016 &#150; December 2016</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:207pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>40% Pro Rata Share</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>January 2017 &#150; December 2017</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:207pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>60% Pro Rata Share</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>January 2018 &#150; December 2018</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:207pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>80% Pro Rata Share</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>January 2019 and after</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:202.5pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>100% Pro Rata Share</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>Notwithstanding the foregoing, if the credit enhancement provided by the Subordinate Certificates doubles (from the initial credit enhancement) Principal Prepayments will be paid pro-rata between the Senior and Subordinate Certificates (subject to the performance triggers described in the prospectus supplement). &nbsp;However, if the credit enhancement provided by the Subordinate Certificates has doubled (subject to the performance triggers described in the prospectus supplement), (i) prior to the Distribution Date in <A NAME="OLE_LINK2"></A>January 2008, the Subordinate Certificates will be entitled to only 50% of their pro rata share of Principal Prepayments or (ii) on or after the Distribution Date in January 2008, the Subordinate Certificates will be entitled to 100% of their pro rata share
 of Principal Prepayments.</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:8pt; color:#000000" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>Any principal not allocated to the Subordinate Certificates will be allocated to the Senior Certificates. &nbsp;In the event the current senior percentage (aggregate principal balance of the Senior Certificates, divided by the aggregate principal balance of the Mortgage Loans) exceeds the applicable initial senior percentage (aggregate principal balance of the Senior Certificates as of the Closing Date, divided by the aggregate principal balance of the Mortgage Loans as of the Cut-off Date), the Senior Certificates will receive all principal prepayments for the Mortgage Loan group, regardless of any prepayment percentages.</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><BR></P>

<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:8pt; font-size:8pt; color:#000000" align=center><I>This Preliminary Term Sheet is provided for information purposes only, and does not constitute an offer to sell, nor a solicitation of an offer to buy, the referenced securities. &nbsp;It does not purport to be all-inclusive or to contain all of the information that a prospective investor may require to make a full analysis of the transaction. &nbsp;All amounts are approximate and subject to change. &nbsp;The information contained herein supersedes information contained in any prior term sheet for this transaction. &nbsp;In addition, the information contained herein will be superseded by information contained in term sheets circulated after the date hereof and by information contained in the Prospectus and Prospectus Supplement for this transaction. &nbsp;An offering may be made only through the delivery of the Prospectus and Prospectus Supplement.</I></P>

<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><I>Allocation of</I></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><I>Realized Losses:</I></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>Any realized losses, other than excess losses, on the Mortgage Loans will be allocated as follows: first, to the Subordinate Certificates in reverse order of their numerical Class designations, in each case until the respective class principal balance has been reduced to zero; and <I>second</I>; to the related Senior Certificates until its class principal balance has been reduced to zero.</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; font-size:6pt; color:#000000" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>Excess losses (bankruptcy, special hazard and fraud losses in excess of the amounts established by the rating agencies) will be allocated to the related Class A Certificates and the related component of the Subordinate Certificates on a pro rata basis.</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><I>Carryover Shortfall</I></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><I>Amount:</I></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>The Class 1-A and Class 2-A Certificates will be entitled to the payment of an amount equal to the sum of (i) the excess, if any, of (a) interest accrued at the Certificate Interest Rate for such Class (without giving effect to the Net WAC Cap) over (b) the amount of interest actually accrued on such Class and (ii) the unpaid portion of any such excess from previous Distribution Dates (and any interest thereon at the certificate interest rate for such Class without giving effect to the Net WAC Cap) (together, the &#147;<B><I>Carryover Shortfall Amount</I></B>&#148;). &nbsp;The Carryover Shortfall Amount will be paid only to the extent of interest otherwise distributable to the Class X-1 Certificates (in the case of the Class 1-A Certificates) and the Class X-2 Certificates (in the case of the C
lass 2-A Certificates). </P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><I>Net WAC Cap:</I></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>The <B><I>&#147;Net WAC Cap&#148;</I></B> for the Mortgage Loans or any Mortgage Loan Group is the weighted average of the Net Mortgage Rates of the related mortgage loans. &nbsp;The <B><I>&#147;Net Mortgage Rate&#148;</I></B> with respect to each mortgage loan is equal to the loan rate less the related servicing fee and trust expense fee rate.</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:126pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-126pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:126pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-126pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><I>Certificates Priority of</I></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-108pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><I>Distributions:</I></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:108pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>Available funds from the Mortgage Loans will be distributed in the following order of priority:</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:144pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-22.5pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>1)</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:144pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>Senior Certificates, accrued and unpaid interest, at the related Certificate Interest Rate from the related Mortgage Loans, <I>provided, however</I>, that any interest otherwise distributable with respect to the Class X-1 and Class X-2 Certificates will be reduced to the extent necessary to pay any Carryover Shortfall Amount below;</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:144pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-22.5pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>2)</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:144pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>Class A-R Certificate, principal, until its balance is reduced to zero;</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:144pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-22.5pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>3)</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:144pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>Concurrently to the Class A Certificates:</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:166.5pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-22.5pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>i)</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:166.5pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>Class 1-A Certificates until the principal balance thereof has been reduced to zero, from the Group 1 Mortgage Loans;</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:166.5pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-22.5pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>ii)</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:166.5pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>Class 2-A Certificates until the principal balance thereof has been reduced to zero, from the Group 2 Mortgage Loans; </P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:166.5pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-22.5pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>iii)</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:166.5pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>Class 3-A Certificates until the principal balance thereof has been reduced to zero, from the Group 3 Mortgage Loans; </P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:166.5pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-22.5pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>iv)</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:166.5pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>Class 4-A Certificates until the principal balance thereof has been reduced to zero, from the Group 4 Mortgage Loans; </P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:144pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-22.5pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>4)</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:144pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>Class 1-A and Class 2-A Certificates, to pay any related Carryover Shortfall Amount, solely from amounts otherwise distributable with respect to the Class X-1 and Class X-2 Certificates, respectively;</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:144pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-22.5pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>5)</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:144pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>p supplementSenior Certificates, in the same order as described above, from the unrelated Mortgage Loan group, principal, to the extent not received from the related Mortgage Loan group;</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:144pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-22.5pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>6)</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:144pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>Class B-1 Certificates, accrued and unpaid interest at the Class B-1 Certificate Interest Rate;</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:144pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-22.5pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>7)</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:144pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>Class B-1 Certificates, principal allocable to such Class;</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:144pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-22.5pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>8)</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:144pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>Class B-2 Certificates, accrued and unpaid interest at the Class B-2 Certificate Interest Rate;</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:144pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-22.5pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>9)</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:144pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>Class B-2 Certificates, principal allocable to such Class;</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:144pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-22.5pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>10)</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:144pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>Class B-3 Certificates, accrued and unpaid interest at the Class B-3 Certificate Interest Rate;</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:144pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-22.5pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>11)</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:144pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>Class B-3 Certificates, principal allocable to such Class;</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:144pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-22.5pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>12)</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:144pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>Class B-4, Class B-5 and Class B-6 Certificates, in sequential order, accrued and unpaid interest at the related Certificate Interest Rate and their respective share of principal allocable to such Classes;</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:144pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-22.5pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify>13)</P>

<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:126pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-126pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=justify><BR></P>

<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:-0.95pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:11pt; font-size:11pt; color:#000000" align=justify>The attached tables and other statistical analyses (the &#147;Computational Materials&#148;) are privileged and intended for use by the addressee only. &nbsp;These Computational Materials have been prepared by Greenwich Capital Markets, Inc. in reliance upon information furnished by the issuer of the securities and its affiliates. &nbsp;These Computational Materials are furnished to you solely by Greenwich Capital Markets, Inc. and not by the issuer of the securities. &nbsp;They may not be provided to any third party other than the addressee&#146;s legal, tax, financial and/or accounting advisors for the purposes of evaluating said material.</P>

<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:-0.95pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:11pt; font-size:11pt; color:#000000" align=justify>Numerous assumptions were used in preparing the Computational Materials which may or may not be reflected therein. &nbsp;As such, no assurance can be given as to the Computational Materials&#146; accuracy, appropriateness or completeness in any particular context; nor as to whether the Computational Materials and/or the assumptions upon which they are based reflect present market conditions or future market performance. &nbsp;These Computational Materials should not be construed as either projections or predictions or as legal, tax, financial or accounting advice.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:-0.95pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:11pt; color:#000000" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:-0.95pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:11pt; font-size:11pt; color:#000000" align=justify>Any weighted average lives, yields and principal payment periods shown in the Computational Materials are based on prepayment assumptions, and changes in such prepayment assumptions may dramatically affect such weighted average lives, yields and principal payment periods. &nbsp;In addition, it is possible that prepayments on the underlying assets will occur at rates slower or faster than the rates shown in the attached Computational Materials. &nbsp;Furthermore, unless otherwise provided, the Computational Materials assume no losses on the underlying assets and no interest shortfall. &nbsp;The specific characteristics of the securities may differ from those shown in the Computational Materials due to differences between the actual underlying assets and the hypothetical underlying assets used in preparing the Computational Materials
. &nbsp;The principal amount and designation of any security described in the Computational Materials are subject to change prior to issuance. &nbsp;Neither Greenwich Capital Markets, Inc. nor any of its affiliates makes any representation or warranty as to the actual rate or timing of payments on any of the underlying assets or the payments or yield on the securities.</P>

<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:12pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10.4pt; padding-left:118.5pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:12pt; font-size:12pt; color:#000000"><B>COMPUTATIONAL MATERIALS DISCLAIMER </B></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:9.95pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:11.5pt; font-size:11.5pt; color:#000000" align=justify>The attached tables and other statistical analyses (the &#147;Computational Materials&#148;) are privileged and intended for use by the addressee only. &nbsp;These Computational Materials have been prepared by Greenwich Capital Markets, Inc. in reliance upon information furnished by the issuer of the securities and its affiliates. &nbsp;These Computational Materials are furnished to you solely by Greenwich Capital Markets, Inc. and not by the issuer of the securities. &nbsp;They may not be provided to any third party other than the addressee&#146;s legal, tax, financial and/or accounting advisors for the purposes of evaluating said material. </P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:9.95pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:11.5pt; font-size:11.5pt; color:#000000" align=justify>Numerous assumptions were used in preparing the Computational Materials which may or may not be reflected therein. &nbsp;As such, no assurance can be given as to the Computational Materials&#146; accuracy, appropriateness or completeness in any particular context; nor as to whether the Computational Materials and/or the assumptions upon which they are based reflect present market conditions or future market performance. &nbsp;These Computational Materials should not be construed as either projections or predictions or as legal, tax, financial or accounting advice. </P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10.7pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:11.5pt; font-size:11.5pt; color:#000000">Any weighted average lives, yields and principal payment periods shown in the Computational Materials are based on prepayments assumptions, and changes in such prepayment assumptions may dramatically affect such weighted average lives, yields and principal payment periods. &nbsp;In addition, it is possible that prepayments on the underlying assets will occur at rates slower or faster than the rates shown in the attached Computational Materials. &nbsp;Furthermore, unless otherwise provided, the Computational Materials assume no losses on the underlying assets and no interest shortfall. &nbsp;The specific characteristics of the securities may differ from those shown in the Computational Materials due to differences between the actual underlying assets and the hypothetical underlying assets used in preparing the Computational Materials. &nbsp;The principal amount an
d designation of any security described in the Computational Materials are subject to change prior to issuance. &nbsp;Neither Greenwich Capital Markets, Inc. nor any of its affiliates makes any representation or warranty as to the actual rate or timing of payments on any of the underlying assets or the payments or yield on the securities. </P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:9.95pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:11.5pt; font-size:11.5pt; color:#000000" align=justify>Although a registration statement (including the Prospectus) relating to the securities discussed in this communication has been filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission and is effective, the final prospectus supplement relating to the securities discussed in this communication has not been filed with Securities and Exchange Commission. &nbsp;This communication shall not constitute an offer to sell or the solicitation of an offer to buy nor shall there be any sale of the securities discussed in this communication in any state in which such offer, solicitation or sale would be unlawful prior to registration or qualification of such securities under the securities laws of any such state. &nbsp;Prospective purchasers are referred to the final prospectus supplement relating to the securities discussed in this communication for definitive Comput
ational Materials and any matter discussed in this communication. &nbsp;Once available, a final prospectus and prospectus supplement may be obtained by contacting the Greenwich Capital Markets, Inc. Trading Desk at (203) 625-6160. </P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10.7pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:11.5pt; font-size:11.5pt; color:#000000" align=justify>Please be advised that the securities described herein may not be appropriate for all investors. &nbsp;Potential investors must be willing to assume, among other things, market price volatility, prepayment, yield curve and interest rate risks. &nbsp;Investors should make every effort to consider the risks of these securities. &nbsp;</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:11.5pt; font-size:11.5pt; color:#000000">If you have received this communication in error, please notify the sending party immediately by telephone and return the original to such party by mail. </P>
